        "order": 38
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_4",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Critics also accused the Lava Jato taskforce of using aggressive tactics to court media attention. Lula was arrested in 2016 using a bench warrant, usually used when a subpoenaed person refuses to attend a hearing, something he had not done. In Peru and Brazil, prosecutors were criticised for the extensive use of pre-trial detention. One Brazilian investigator forbade the rector of a university from entering his campus, and briefly imprisoned him on suspicion of corruption. The rector committed suicide soon after. He was innocent.",
        "bbox": [
          0.06100628200291091,
          0.3618551589215137,
          0.3423652335391654,
          0.5305232556621586
        ],
        "order": 41
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_72",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Few people in Brazil want to talk about corruption anymore, except to express disdain for Lava Jato. Gilmar Mendes, a Supreme Court judge, dismisses it as the product of foreign interference, \"propaganda\" by the media, and \"anti-corruption fighters [who] like money a lot\".",
        "bbox": [
          0.6595351029989153,
          0.3735119047199012,
          0.9408418979437235,
          0.46511627897469027
        ],
        "order": 42
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_74",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The blowback on Lava Jato is bipartisan. Mr Moro, now a senator, faces two trials which could bar him from office. One, concerning alleged campaign-finance abuses, was filed by Mr Bolsonaro's party. The other, which alleges that Mr Moro committed fraud as part of an old plea deal, was launched by Mr Toffoli. Mr Dallagnol lost his seat in Congress after a decision by an electoral court on a technicality. He notes that the deciding judge was himself investigated by Lava Jato, and that lower courts had ruled in his favour. Mr Moro says both accusations against him are baseless.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6558317436084375,
          0.494186046614973,
          0.9407265775738087,
          0.6773313492322856
        ],
        "order": 44
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Politicians pounced on these cracks. \"Lava Jato was like the Jacobin moment of the French Revolution,\" says Marco Bastos of Southern Pulse, a consultancy. Brazilians gawked at their televisions as a parade of politicians were figuratively guillotined. Then the old guard struck back.",
        "bbox": [
          0.06118546831529259,
          0.5334302327694957,
          0.344168263705461,
          0.6235465115618996
        ],
        "order": 45
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_42",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Spend money to make money",
        "bbox": [
          0.37093690634683013,
          0.5872093025561069,
          0.5736137578023096,
          0.5974702378967158
        ],
        "order": 47
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_43",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Selected Foreign Corrupt Practices Act cases",
        "bbox": [
          0.37093690654026584,
          0.6001984129142135,
          0.6022944486541255,
          0.6119186047789539
        ],
        "order": 48
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_45",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Il Gross profits from bribes, Sm",
        "bbox": [
          0.47227533752938744,
          0.6177325580117439,
          0.6214149110365782,
          0.6294642857405117
        ],
        "order": 49
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_44",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Bribes paid, Sm",
        "bbox": [
          0.3709369033843549,
          0.6191860468572213,
          0.46080305882087136,
          0.629464285520819
        ],
        "order": 50
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_46",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "• Total fine, Sm",
        "bbox": [
          0.3709369044345422,
          0.6321924604010253,
          0.44933078460306136,
          0.6409883717585416
        ],
        "order": 51
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Legislators may have ousted Ms Rousseff because they felt she was doing too little to protect them. Romero Jucá, a senator, was caught on a wiretap before her impeachment, telling a political ally: \"This shit has to be fixed...the government needs to be changed to stanch the bleeding.\" He said his words had been taken out of context.",
        "bbox": [
          0.05927342455457723,
          0.6509584943128145,
          0.34236006948572295,
          0.7544642858061293
        ],
        "order": 53
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_47",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Odebrecht 2001-16",
        "bbox": [
          0.37093690097771914,
          0.6555059523620833,
          0.4665391965366212,
          0.6642441858186192
        ],
        "order": 54
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_48",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "788",
        "bbox": [
          0.3690248565407585,
          0.670058139767076,
          0.38814531490602283,
          0.6773255813085055
        ],
        "order": 55
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_75",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "On February 26th a different judge on Brazil's Supreme Court authorised companies that had signed leniency agreements during Lava Jato to renegotiate the terms. They were given 60 days to do so, during which time all fines related to the case have been suspended. The companies claimed they felt coerced into signing the agreements, which \"jeopardise their existence\".",
        "bbox": [
          0.6596558340153851,
          0.6787790697462399,
          0.9407265775738087,
          0.7966269839164599
        ],
        "order": 56
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.09_page_029_49",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "3,336",
        "bbox": [
          0.369024856642858,
          0.6816860467438203,
          0.39579349810538933,
